Ahead of school resumption, 5,697 teachers in public and private schools across the 25 local government areas of Delta State have been trained on COVID-19 protocols in the schools. Commissioner for Basic and Secondary Education, Chief Patrick Ukah, who monitored the training exercise at St. Patrick’s College, Asaba, yesterday said that the Governor Ifeanyi Okowa led-administration was committed to safeguarding the health of residents, especially teachers and school children in the state. The programme, according to Ukah, was aimed at ensuring that the trained teachers would in turn train others in their various schools, towards ensuring adequate safety of school children from contracting the coronavirus. Chief Ukah stated that the visit was informed by the need to encourage the teachers and to ascertain their level of commitment and participation in the training. He added that the state government would provide critical measures to avert the spread of the coronavirus in the wake of schools resumption. He reiterated that government would supply items such as hand sanitizers, face masks and other items needed for curtailing the virus in learning environment, adding that sickbays would be provided for schools where non was available. The two-day training programme is taking place in three centres in each of the 25 local governments of the state to ensure that social distance is maintained. 